config APP_PORT
	tristate "LEGO Powered Up I/O port utility"
	default n
	---help---
		CLI for the LEGO Powered Up I/O port driver
		(/dev/legoport0..5).  Subcommands:

		    list / info <P> / wait <P> / stats   (Issue #42 DCM)
		    pwm <P> set/coast/brake/status       (Issue #80 H-bridge)
		    lump status                          (Issue #43 LUMP, global)
		    lump <P> info/set-mode/send/watch    (Issue #43 LUMP, per-port)
		    lump-hw dump                         (CONFIG_LEGO_LUMP_DIAG)

		Port arguments accept A..F / a..f / 0..5.

		WARNING: driving PWM into a non-motor LUMP device (SPIKE
		Color sensor type 61, Ultrasonic type 62, Force type 63,
		etc.) can damage it.  Motors are safe — both passive
		(M-motor 45303, Train motor 88011) and active SPIKE motors
		(M=48, L=49, S=65) are driven by the same H-bridge that
		pybricks uses.
